race.comment: VERONA ROSE (7) gets a dream setup first-up with a stack of speed engaged. She was excellent in the spring against top-tier 3YOs and looks to have returned in great order off a sharp Warwick Farm trial. She'll let the leaders cut at each other and be looking to swoop over the top late. LAZZURA (1) fits a similar profile - a talented mare resuming who kicked off her spring with an arrogant win in the Let's Elope. McDonald will let her drift back and blend in, and she'll be charging if the race unfolds as expected. COUNTYOURBLESSINGS (8) was enormous in the MM Fillies & Mares at the Gold Coast, savaging the line to miss by a head. She gets in light with Lloyd sticking and is another who will relish a brutal tempo. Expect her to burst through late. LILAC (10) resumes and is pure speed. Two trials have her ready to fly, and she'll give a sight though she won't be alone up front. MANAAL (2) returns over a trip short of her best but has the class to flash late if the leaders overcook it.
